<!-- GLOSSARY -->
<section id="glossary">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="sec-head fi">
      <span class="sec-tag">// 08 / terminology</span>
      <h2 class="sec-title">TRADING <span class="y">GLOSSARY</span></h2>
      <p class="sec-desc">The language of markets. Know these terms before you read a chart or place a trade.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="glos-search-wrap fi">
      <input type="text" id="glossSearch" placeholder="Search glossary terms or definitions..." autocomplete="off" />
    </div>
    <div class="glos-grid" id="glosGrid">
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Support</div><div class="glos-def">A price level where buying interest prevents further decline. Historical floors where demand exceeds supply.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Resistance</div><div class="glos-def">A price level where selling pressure prevents further advance. Historical ceilings where supply exceeds demand.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Trend</div><div class="glos-def">Uptrend: higher highs &amp; higher lows. Downtrend: lower highs &amp; lower lows. Sideways: no clear direction.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Stop Loss</div><div class="glos-def">A predefined exit price that limits your loss. Non-negotiable. Moving your stop to avoid a loss is how accounts get blown.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Risk/Reward</div><div class="glos-def">Potential profit ÷ potential loss. A 1:2 R:R means risking $100 to make $200. Minimum acceptable is 1:1.5.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Position Sizing</div><div class="glos-def">Calculating how many shares/contracts to buy based on your risk per trade. The most important mechanical skill in trading.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Drawdown</div><div class="glos-def">Peak-to-trough decline in your account. A 50% drawdown requires a 100% gain to recover. Manage it obsessively.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Breakout</div><div class="glos-def">Price moving decisively beyond a key S/R level on increased volume. Confirms a new directional move.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Fakeout</div><div class="glos-def">A false breakout — price briefly pierces a level then reverses. Designed to trigger stop losses before reversing.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Divergence</div><div class="glos-def">Price makes a new high/low but an indicator doesn't confirm it. One of the strongest signals in technical analysis.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Confluence</div><div class="glos-def">Multiple technical factors aligning at the same price. S/R + Fibonacci + EMA = high-confluence setup. More factors = higher probability.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Backtesting</div><div class="glos-def">Testing your strategy on historical data to evaluate past performance. Essential before committing real capital.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Expectancy</div><div class="glos-def">(Win% × Avg Win) − (Loss% × Avg Loss). Positive over hundreds of trades = a real edge.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">VWAP Bias</div><div class="glos-def">Price above VWAP = bullish intraday sentiment. Below = bearish. TrendTrooper uses this as an intraday filter.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Webhook</div><div class="glos-def">HTTP POST request TradingView sends to TrendTrooper when an alert fires. Contains the full signal payload.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Paper Trading</div><div class="glos-def">Simulated trading with virtual money. No real financial risk. Always validate a strategy here before going live.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">Liquidity</div><div class="glos-def">How easily an asset can be bought or sold without moving price. High liquidity = tight spreads, easy fills.</div></div>
      <div class="glos fi"><div class="glos-term">ATR Stop</div><div class="glos-def">Stop-loss set at Entry ± (ATR × multiplier). Adapts to current volatility. TrendTrooper uses 1.5–2.5× ATR.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

